From: qinf-build <build@qinf.local>
Subject: [PATCH] qinf: add ggml_deltanet_post_state op (Phase 3 — real impl)

PR 4.2.A — qinf downstream patch.

Adds GGML_OP_DELTANET_POST_STATE end-to-end on the CPU backend with the
real fused forward-compute. Replaces the chained 4-op DeltaNet decode
post-state graph (rms_norm + mul(w_norm) + silu(z) + mul) with a single
op that fuses all 4 into one per-row pass.

Equivalence verified by tests/unit/test_deltanet_post_state.cpp:
  decode-shape 128×32×1×1 — max_abs=2.4e-7 max_rel=2.3e-7
(F32 rounding floor; well inside the 1e-5/1e-4 tolerance budget.)

This patch must be applied AFTER 0001-qinf-patch-sentinel.patch (the
sentinel offsets ggml.h by 2 lines; this patch's context is relative to
the post-0001 state). patches/apply-all.sh enforces lexical order.

Files touched:
  ggml/include/ggml.h          — op enum + builder declaration
  ggml/src/ggml.c              — name string, symbol string, OP_COUNT bump,
                                 builder impl
  ggml/src/ggml-cpu/ops.h      — forward-compute declaration
  ggml/src/ggml-cpu/ops.cpp    — forward-compute (fused rms_norm + mul + silu + mul)
  ggml/src/ggml-cpu/ggml-cpu.c — dispatch case + n_tasks case

Metal backend deliberately not modified — supports_op default returns false
for unknown ops, which routes the op to the CPU backend automatically. Real
Metal kernel lands in Phase 4.

